                            <comment id="12572" author="urubatan" created="Mon, 14 Mar 2005 03:50:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the costumized version of AbstractPathMapHandlerMapping&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15946" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 3 Jan 2006 21:41:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This should already be solved in 2.0 M1. The AutowireCapableBeanFactory interface has a new &quot;createBean&quot; method there, which performs full initialization of the bean, including bean post processors (in contrast to the existing &quot;autowire&quot; method). This is the appropriate way to address this issue: It&apos;s not just about the bean post processors, it&apos;s about applying the full initialization cycle to any given plain bean class or instance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please give 2.0 M1 a try and let me know whether it works for you there!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
